<HEADLINE>
FT  16 AUG 93 / Construction Contracts: Upgrading RAF garrison in Yorkshire
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
TRAFALGAR HOUSE CONSTRUCTION MANAGEMENT has secured two new project
management contracts worth Pounds 11m.
The largest is a Pounds 8.7m project to oversee the redevelopment of the
RAF's Catterick Garrison in North Yorkshire as part of the Ministry of
Defence's Options For Change programme. When the two-year contract is
completed the base will provide a home for two army regiments currently
based in Germany.
The second contract is for a Pounds 2.2m cookery school at HMS Raleigh, the
new entry training establishment for the Royal Navy at Torpoint, Cornwall.
</TEXT>
