<HEADLINE>
FT  16 AUG 93 / Mitterrand hits out at speculators
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   PARIS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
MR Francois Mitterrand, French president, has denounced speculators for
triggering the recent currency crisis and called for a speeding up of the
single European currency, Reuter reports from Paris.
In an interview with the French daily newspaper Sud-Ouest released
yesterday, he called speculation a challenge to democracy. 'I find it insane
and immoral that speculation, using billions of dollars, can have its way
against states representing their people's interests and upset the daily
life of millions of people.'
Mr Mitterrand said speculators had targeted the European monetary system
rather than the franc and the system should be strengthened.
He said German Chancellor Helmut Kohl's recent suggestion that the EC might
not achieve a single currency by the 1999 target date should be seen as a
statement of difficulties lying ahead rather than a sign of fading
enthusiasm for monetary unity.
