FT  16 AUG 93 / World News in Brief: European monetary system
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Currencies in the grid continued to draw apart, two weeks after the reform
of the exchange rate mechanism. The strongest currency, the Dutch guilder,
is now separated from the weakest, the Danish krone, by 8.43 percentage
points, more than half the permitted divergence of 15 per cent. The D-Mark
was nearing the level where central bank intervention would be necessary to
reduce its value.
