<HEADLINE>
FT  14 AUG 93 / Two men barred in Fimbra probe
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
FIMBRA, the self-regulating organisation for financial intermediaries,
announced yesterday that it had suspended the registration of Mr Paul
Hogarth and Mr David Warnock of Bankhall Investment Management of
Altrincham, Cheshire.
It said it had issued a Rule Seven direction against the two men ordering
them to cease conducting investment business 'while investigations continue
into the transfer abroad of investment funds in circumstances which make it
difficult to value those funds'.
Bankhall Investment gained Fimbra membership in 1988 and is classed as
Category Three. That means it can arrange transactions through a dealer but
not act as a principal or handle clients' money.
