<HEADLINE>
FT  14 AUG 93 / Food &amp; Drink: Cut-price Petrus - Appetisers
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By EDMUND PENNING-ROWSELL and GILES MCDONAGH
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
A sign of the times in Bordeaux is the just-released, greatly reduced
opening price of Chateau Petrus 1992, as offered by its UK agents, Corney &amp;
Barrow, London EC2 (071-251 4051). In advance of a very large but mostly wet
vintage, not only was severe summer pruning undertaken, but from the
beginning of September the whole 11 hectare vineyard was covered by plastic
sheeting - a costly operation. Picking took place on three sunny afternoons
between September 23 and October 1. The result was 3,000 cases of 12.8' wine
 -25 per cent fewer cases than normal. No Petrus 1991 was offered, but
compared with opening in-bond-London prices of Pounds 1,150, a case for the
1989 and Pounds 1,050 for the 1990, the 1992 is offered at Pounds 550 - as
the quantity is limited, on allocation.
* * *
Invergordon Distillers recently invited a number of drinks writers to the
Hebridean island of Jura to select a special release at cask strength. We
nosed 20 whiskies at between 54' and 63', and now 200 bottles of this
'critics' choice' whisky have been released for sale. The 20-year-old whisky
(54') has a pleasant, nutty character from refilled sherry hogshead.
Enquiries to Invergordon (031-554-4404). UK price Pounds 39.95, including
P&amp;P.
* * *
Since my article on tawny ports appeared last week the excellent port house
of Niepoort has found a UK distributor. Enquiries to Bibendum (071-722
5577).
</TEXT>
