<HEADLINE>
FT  14 AUG 93 / UK Company News: Portmeirion 12% up at Pounds 1.6m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
PROFITS before tax of Portmeirion Potteries (Holdings) rose to Pounds 1.59m
for the six months ended June 30, an improvement of 12 per cent over last
time's Pounds 1.42m.
The figures benefited from a sharp reduction in interest charges to Pounds
27,000 (Pounds 220,000), which reflected lower interest rates on lower bank
borrowings.
Turnover for the opening half year increased from Pounds 10.43m to Pounds
11.37m but at the operating level profits were static at Pounds 1.54m having
been adversely affected by difficulties experienced in the installation of
new glazing equipment.
Earnings per share rose from 8.89p to 9.88p and the interim dividend is a
same-again 2.25p.
Looking ahead, the directors said some export markets remained difficult.
They added, however, that the major markets in the UK and the US were
'performing well' and that profit margins were expected to improve now that
production difficulties were being overcome.
The shares rose 4p to 399p.
</TEXT>
