FT  14 AUG 93 / National Savings contribution falls
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
NATIONAL Savings contributed Pounds 103m to government funding in July
compared with Pounds 220m in June. Gross sales of Pounds 638m were
outweighed by repayments of Pounds 727m, with accrued interest amounting to
Pounds 192m.
Fixed-interest certificates contributed the most to the total, at Pounds
53m, followed by capital bonds at Pounds 38m. The total amount invested in
National Savings at the end of July was Pounds 44.9bn.
