<HEADLINE>
FT  13 AUG 93 / International Company News: Coles Myer outlines plans for
expansion
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By BRUCE JACQUES
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   SYDNEY
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
COLES MYER, the Australian retailing group, has announced plans to spend
ADollars 4.15bn (USDollars 2.8bn) over the next five years on a store
expansion plan aimed at lifting sales and margins, writes Bruce Jacques in
Sydney.
Mr Peter Bartels, chief executive, said the programme - the largest
retailing expansion in Australia - would involve building 421 new stores,
refurbishing 1,136 others and expanding and building more than 12 shopping
centres.
'The investment programme is a major plank in our strategy to maximise
future profitability and returns to shareholders,' Mr Bartels said, adding
that it would be financed entirely from internal funds.
Mr Bartels said new and refurbished stores produced sales increases of
between 10 per cent and 30 per cent, improving investment returns.
